        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "BACKGROUND"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.1,
                "text": "In order to maintain continued participant and research support for research studies it is important that anyone involved in a research study at Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust (MEHT) who changes role or discontinues working on a research study follows this Standard Operating Procedure (SOP)."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "PURPOSE"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.1,
                "text": "This SOP outlines the procedure to undertake when staff member changes role or discontinue working on a research study."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.0,
                "text": "APPLICABLE TO"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 3.1,
                "text": "Any Trust employee involved with clinical research sponsored or hosted by MEHT including, but not limited to, Chief Investigators (CI), Principal Investigators (PI), Consultants, Co-investigators, Clinical Trial Pharmacists, Research Managers, Statisticians, Research Nurses, Research Midwives, Allied Health Professionals, Trial Coordinators, R&D Department & Data Managers."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.0,
                "text": "RESPONSIBILITIES"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.1,
                "text": "Planned - The employee's line manager is responsible for ensuring the handover outlined below is undertaken. The CI/PI is responsible for ensuring the member of staff has been crossed through on the delegation log and it is countering signed. If it is the CI/PI that is leaving, R&D will liaise with the sponsor and identify suitable replacement where possible. The Data manager is responsible for disabling exiting staff's access to the research database"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.2,
                "text": "Unplanned \u2013 R&D will work with CI/PI/Sponsor to ensure continued safety of research participants and identify replacements. The Data Manager is responsible for disabling unplanned exiting staff from the research database"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.0,
                "text": "PROCEDURE"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 27,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "Planned Staff Exit"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 28,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "5.1.1 When a member of staff plans to discontinue working on a research study because they are leaving the Research and Development (R&D) department or Trust they should complete the following tasks in an appropriate timeframe;"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "\u25cf Handover any research studies to a delegated individual, providing a detailed schedule of recruitment processes and follow-up of participants"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "\u25cf Ensure they have signed off the delegation log and that the Principal Investigator (PI) has countersigned their exit"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 31,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "\u25cf Inform the Data Manager so their research database access can be disabled"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "5.1.2 In addition if it is the PI planning on leaving the Trust the PI should inform R&D as soon as practicable suggesting a suitable replacement, the R&D department will then liaise with the proposed PI, trial centre and Research Network as appropriate, to change the PI."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 33,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "5.1.3 The PI, with the Site-Coordinator, will ensure that anyone taking over this role has sufficient training to undertake the role and is delegated to do so."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 34,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.2,
                "text": "Unplanned Staff Exit"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 35,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "5.2.1 Where a member of staff is suddenly unavailable and their expected unavailability is for more than three months (e.g. long term sickness) the PI and R&D may need to take urgent action to ensure the continued safety of research participants and the continued smooth running of the research study."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 36,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "5.2.2 The PI will ensure the exiting staff member is off the delegation log, this may also require a File Note to clarify events."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 37,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "5.2.3 The Data Manager will temporarily disable the exiting staff member's access to the research database."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 38,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "5.2.4 If it is the PI who is unexpectedly unavailable a local collaborator will temporarily take on the PI's role to ensure continued safety of the research participants, the R&D department will liaise with the trial centre to discuss long-term arrangements."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 39,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "5.2.5 The PI with the Site-Coordinator will ensure that anyone taking over this role has sufficient training to undertake the role and is delegated to do so."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 40,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.3,
                "text": "Change in roles"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 41,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "If a member of staff changes their role then sections 5.1 Planned Staff Exit or 5.2 Unplanned Staff Exit should be followed as appropriate."
            }
        },
        {
